":"recall","cmd":"describe"},{"id":"0580-2019OctNov-Paper21-Q22","paper":"2019OctNov-Paper21","qnum":22,"marks":4,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.2","d":2,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Area and perimeter","qtype":"area and perimeter","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/19 Q22","year":2019,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A pipe is completely full of water.\nWater flows through the pipe at a speed of 1.2 m/s into a tank.\nThe cross-section of the pipe has an area of 6 cm$^{2}$.\n\nCalculate the number of litres of water flowing into the tank in 1 hour.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"litres"}},{"id":"0580-2019OctNov-Paper21-Q23","paper":"2019OctNov-Paper21","qnum":23,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.2","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/19 Q23","year":2019,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Complete each of the following statements.\n\n\\[\n\\xi = \\{0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6\\} \\quad A = \\{0, 2, 4, 5, 6\\} \\quad B = \\{1, 2, 5\\}\n\\]\n\nA ∪ B = \\{  \\}\n\nn(B) = \n\n\\{0, 4, 6\\} =  ∪ \n\n\\{2, 4\\}  A","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"complete","answer":{"type":"multiline","lines":5,"layout":"column","template":"____\\n____\\n____\\n____\\n____"}},{"id":"0580-2019OctNov-Paper21-Q24","paper":"2019OctNov-Paper21","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.13","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Functions","qtype":"functions","g":"function","src":"0580/21/O/N/19 Q24","year":2019,"session":"OctNov","tex":"\\[\nf(x) = 3x - 5 \\quad g(x) = 2^{x}\n\\]\n\n(a) Find fg(3).\n\n(b) Find f$^{-1}(x)$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2,"answer":{"type":"number","prefix":"f⁻¹(x) ="}}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019OctNov-Paper21-Q25","paper":"2019OctNov-Paper21","qnum":25,"marks":4,"topics":["Coordinate geometry","Transformations and vectors"],"s":"3.1","d":2,"cat":"coord","topic":"Coordinates","qtype":"coordinates reading/plotting","g":"graph","src":"0580/21/O/N/19 Q25","year":2019,"session":"OctNov","tex":"O is the origin, $\\overrightarrow{OP} = 2\\overrightarrow{OA}$, $\\overrightarrow{OQ} = 3\\overrightarrow{OB}$ and $\\overrightarrow{PM} = \\overrightarrow{MQ}$.\n\n$\\overrightarrow{OP} = \\overrightarrow{p}$ and $\\overrightarrow{OQ} = \\overrightarrow{q}$.\n\nFind, in terms of $\\overrightarrow{p}$ and $\\overrightarrow{q}$, in its simplest form,\n\n(a) $\\overrightarrow{BA}$,\n\n$\\overrightarrow{BA} = $ \n\n(b) the position vector of M.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2019OctNov-Paper21-Q26","paper":"2019OctNov-Paper21","qnum":26,"marks":5,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.12","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Rates","qtype":"rates","g":"mixed","src":"0580/21/O/N/19 Q26","year":2019,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A car travels at 20 m/s for 15 seconds before it comes to rest by decelerating at 2.5 m/s$^{2}$.\n\nFind the total distance travelled.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find","answer":{"type":"number","suffix":"m"}}]